Gay Village and the streets of Kamloops, BC this lively and dynamic semi-autobiographical novel dives deeply into gender and queerness, class and privilege, and the realities of aging. It is a dynamic and engaging hybrid, stylistically daring while remaining intimate and human. Leaping through time and mixing the playfully serious with the seriously playful, DR SAD blends poetry with prose and finds the humour in despair in one complete, glittering tragedy of triumph  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGay menvFiction. 0aMiddle-aged menvFiction. 0aTeachersvFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aGay village.  aHIV.  aHIV/AIDS.  aKamloops.  aToronto.  aWriting.  aart.  aauto-fiction.  abook lover gifts.  abooks about aids.  abooks about creative writing.  abooks about hiv.  acollection.  acreative writing.  adrama.  afiction books.  afiction.  agay Kamloops.  agay books.  agay fiction.  agender identity.  agift books.  alanguage.  aliterary fiction.  apost-colonial.  aqueer fiction.  aqueer identity.  arealistic fiction.  ateaching.  auniversity.  awhat should I read next.  awriting poetry book.  awriting.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311127253508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2020z978311127473740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781773851044?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781773851044423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781773851044/original  a978-3-11-127253-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-127473-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles